I was not upset and asked if they would be able to remake it because it was not what I purchased.  The young woman behind the counter was not happy and was very rude.  She did not say anything to me, rolled her eyes, and threw the original drink in the trash so dramatically that it splashed onto the counter.  She remade it and slammed it on the counter and the coffee spilled out onto the lid.  I said thank you and she turned her back to me and she walked away.  It was 9am and the store was not busy. I tend to extend grace in these types of situations, but there were no external factors to contribute to the behavior exemplified.
